**Franking credits** (imputation credits) are tax credits attached to dividends paid by Australian companies that have already paid 30% corporate tax. Shareholders include the grossed-up dividend in their income and use the franking credit to offset their income tax — preventing double taxation.

For a fully franked $700 dividend, the attached franking credit is $300 (30/70 of the cash dividend). The grossed-up income is $1,000. At a 32% marginal rate, net additional tax is only $20 — making fully franked Australian shares highly tax-efficient. Retirees and SMSFs in pension phase can receive the full $300 credit as a cash refund.
